42
00:03:13,022 --> 00:03:29,535
[SPEAKER_24]: On March 7, 1940, city officials and citizens came together to name the auditorium in memory of Lieutenant Commander Godfrey Chevalier, who, remember, was a pioneer in naval aviation.

43
00:03:30,758 --> 00:03:32,359
[SPEAKER_24]: and a war hero from Medford.

44
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:41,665
[SPEAKER_24]: One of his most important accomplishments was when he was the first aviator to land a plane on a moving ship.

45
00:03:43,686 --> 00:03:58,035
[SPEAKER_24]: About a month after that event, unfortunately, Godfrey Chevalier was in an accident, a plane crash in Virginia, which resulted in his death at age 33.

46
00:03:59,898 --> 00:04:00,318
[SPEAKER_24]: That was in 1922.

47
00:04:00,898 --> 00:04:07,760
[SPEAKER_24]: We're proud of Godfrey Chevalier and of the history of the Chevalier Theatre.

48
00:04:07,780 --> 00:04:10,681
