52
00:04:27,610 --> 00:04:33,092
[SPEAKER_24]: and especially wonderful stage performances by the Medford-based Mystic Players.

53
00:04:34,612 --> 00:04:41,755
[SPEAKER_24]: When the high school was relocated to Winthrop Street in 1970, the history and condition of the building changed dramatically.

54
00:04:42,855 --> 00:04:48,757
[SPEAKER_24]: It was vacant, ignored, and fell into major disrepair.

55
00:04:53,199 --> 00:04:55,340
[SPEAKER_24]: It was not until 1980 when the city of Medford

56
00:04:57,270 --> 00:05:08,458
[SPEAKER_24]: the property owners of the building, upon receiving a $1.2 million grant from the State, established a Civic Auditorium and Convention Center Commission.

57
00:05:09,639 --> 00:05:26,551
[SPEAKER_24]: Under the direction of this group of volunteers, major improvements such as an elevator, new lobby and restrooms, and a stair tower and stage right were made

58
00:05:28,718 --> 00:05:31,779
[SPEAKER_24]: in compliance with ADA regulations.

59
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:52,204
